# SabChnagaSi 🛡️

A command-line interface (CLI) tool to check if a PDF file is AI-generated (e.g., written by ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, etc.) or human-written. 

Named **SabChnagaSi** (meaning *"Everything is fine"* in Punjabi/Hindi), it gives you a quick, colored verdict on whether your documents are genuine or machine-made!

---

## Features

- **Global CLI Usage:** Install once and run `SabChnagaSi <filename>.pdf` from any directory in your command prompt.
- **Two Modes of Operation:**
  1. **API-Based Check (Recommended):** Uses highly accurate APIs from **GPTZero** or **Sapling**. Fast, lightweight, and regularly updated for the latest model capabilities.
  2. **FREE Check (Offline):** Runs a local sequence classification model (`Hello-SimpleAI/chatgpt-detector-roberta`) directly on your machine. 100% free and private.
- **Automatic Text Extraction:** Directly parses and cleans raw text from PDFs before running checks.
- **Long Document Support:** Automatically chunks long documents to fit model token limits and averages detection scores.

---

## Installation

Follow these steps to clone and install the tool globally on your system:

### 1. Clone the Repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/1305abhi/Sabchnagesi.git
cd Sabchnagesi
```

### 2. Install Globally
Using your terminal (Command Prompt, PowerShell, or bash), install the package in editable mode:
```bash
pip install -e .
```

*This command automatically registers `SabChnagaSi` as a global executable on your system by mapping it to Python's Scripts directory.*

---

## Usage & Onboarding

### First-Run Setup
The first time you run the tool on any PDF, it will guide you through an interactive setup:

```bash
SabChnagaSi report.pdf
```

**Output:**
```
=== SabChnagaSi Onboarding Configuration ===
Choose your AI check method:
  [1] API Check (Requires a key for GPTZero or Sapling. High accuracy, very fast)
  [2] FREE Check (Downloads local AI model Hello-SimpleAI/chatgpt-detector-roberta. Offline, 100% free)
Enter choice (1 or 2): 
```

- **If you select `1` (API):** It will prompt you to input your credentials in the format `platform_name,API_KEY` (e.g., `gptzero,your_api_key_here`).
- **If you select `2` (FREE):** It will configure local model evaluation. The first time you scan, it will download about ~500MB of model weights.

### Global Command execution
You can navigate to any folder on your computer (e.g. `Desktop/Case/`) and run the tool directly by passing the file name:

```bash
SabChnagaSi my_case_file.pdf
```

### Resetting Configuration
If you want to switch detection modes (e.g., switch from GPTZero to FREE local check) or update your API key:
```bash
SabChnagaSi --reset
```

---

## Detection Verdicts

Based on the probability percentage of AI-generated content, SabChnagaSi gives the following colored statuses:

| Color | AI Score | Punjabi/Hindi Verdict | English Translation |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **🟢 Green** | `< 20%` | **Sab Chnaga Si!** | Everything is fine! Written by a Human. |
| **🟡 Yellow** | `20% – 50%` | **Thoda Gadbad Hai!** | Suspicious / Mixed writing. |
| **🔴 Red** | `> 50%` | **Daya, Kuch Toh Gadbad Hai!** | Likely generated by an AI model. |

---

## Development & Dependencies
Dependencies are managed automatically upon installation. They include:
- `pypdf` for parsing PDF documents.
- `requests` for making external API calls.
- `transformers` & `torch` for running the local RoBERTa model.
- `click` for command-line prompt interfaces and terminal coloring.
